# pouch — boundary-line patch series against vendored musl 1.2.5.
#
# quilt-style ordered list: one patch file per line, applied top-to-bottom
# from the musl tree root. Lines starting with '#' are comments; blank lines
# are ignored. See README.md in this directory for the discipline.
#
# Invariant P-4 (POUCH-DESIGN.md §11): every patch touches ONLY musl's lower
# half + the syscall seam — never the portable upper half (string / stdio /
# stdlib / math / ...). See docs/reference/78-pouch.md for the per-directory
# UPPER / LOWER / SEAM boundary-line inventory.
#
# The series is empty at sub-chunk 2 (pouch-musl-vendor). The boundary-line
# replacement lands across Phase 6 sub-chunks 3-12 (pouch-kernel-auxv through
# pouch-signals) — see docs/POUCH-DESIGN.md §14.
